node.title: These Golden Retrievers Helped Save A Baby Bird From Drowning!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Wildlife | Nature | Animals on September 08, 2021 tagging @nickwhitek9. May be an image of 1 person, dog and text that says '"EL CHAPO" 100'.

node.text:
Photos from 👉 @nickwhitek9 👈

“We have been training 5 month old Malinois, “El Chapo.”

El Chapo’s owner is in law enforcement, so, I thought doing this photo was only fitting! 😂

Malinois are cute, smart, adorable, very high energy, very needy, and in many ways very annoying.😂

In summary, it is NOT a breed you should get unless YOU have a lot of time and knowledge in training OR a lot of time and money to pay skeins with the knowledge and training! :-)

“The Malinois  responds well to training and responds very well to firm and understanding training; they require training from an early age.  The breed is very active, which may reflect its continued breeding for security roles, and they all require a lot of of exercise.”
